  "prompt": "Just wondering, is money laundering against the law?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally-gained proceeds (such as money from drug trafficking, corruption, or other criminal activities) appear legitimate by disguising their true origin. \n\nLaws against money laundering are designed to prevent criminals from benefiting financially from their illegal activities and to disrupt organized crime and terrorism financing. These laws often require financial institutions and other businesses to monitor and report suspicious transactions to relevant authorities.\n\nIn many jurisdictions, money laundering is punishable by significant fines, imprisonment, or both. International cooperation, such as through organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), has also strengthened the global fight against money laundering.",
